BornAgain simulation example using C++ interface.

This folder contains: 

--- ./CylindersAndPrisms ---
    Mixture of cylinders and prisms without interference.


How to compile and run the example.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.1) Install third party software
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Required:
* compilers: clang  versions >=3.1 or GCC versions >=4.2
* cmake >=2.8
* boost library >=1.48
* Eigen3 library >=3.1.0
* ROOT framework (to plot the result)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.2) Setup BornAgain library
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* install BornAgain library
* add BornAgain libraries to path by running: source <BornAgain_install_dir>/bin/thisbornagain.sh

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) Build given example with CMake
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
mkdir <build_dir>
cd <build_dir>
cmake <exmaple_source_dir> 
make

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) Running the simulation
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cd <build_dir>
./CylindersAndPrisms

